Title: Almond Joy Overnight Oats
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1/3 cup oats

  • 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk

  • 1/3 cup coconut Greek yogurt

  • 1 scoop chocolate protein powder

  • 1/2 tbsp shredded coconut

  • 1 tbsp dark chocolate chips

  • 1/2 tsp cocoa powder

  • 1/2 tbsp sliced almonds

Directions:

  1. In a mason jar, add the almond milk and protein powder.

  2. Tighten the lid and shake it so the protein powder combines with the milk.

  3. Add other ingredients.

  4. Close the lid and shake to combine.

  5. Place your jar in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.

  6. Stir before eating and enjoy!

Nutrition Data:

1 Serving: 114 g, Calories: 389, Fat: 11 g, Carbohydrates: 39 g, Fiber: 5 g, Protein: 35 g

Fitomics Almond Joy Overnight Oats

Title: Healthier Breakfast Burrito
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 whole wheat tortilla

  • 2 scrambled eggs

  • 1/4 cup turkey sausage

  • 1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese

  • 1/2 cup spinach

Directions:

  1. Cook the eggs and sausage first in separate pans.

  2. Add the spinach in the pan with the eggs.

  3. Once those are cooked, heat the tortilla in the microwave for 5 seconds.

  4. Then build the burrito using eggs with spinach first, then sausage, and adding cheese on top.

  5. Fold tightly and enjoy!

Title: Healthier Breakfast Sandwich
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 Multigrain English Muffin

  • 3 tbsp egg whites, cooked

  • 1 light Laughing Cow cheese wedge

  • 1 Turkey Sausage patty

Directions:

  1. For the egg whites, use a muffin pan and pour 3 tbsp in each tin.

  3. While those are cooking, heat the English muffin and cheese in a toaster oven and microwave the turkey sausage patty according to the package directions.

  4. Then stack the egg white muffin and sausage patty on the English muffin.

Description:

  • 1 cup egg whites

  • 1/2 cup spinach, chopped

Title: Greek Turkey Burgers
Description:
Ingredients:

Turkey Burgers:

  • 24 oz ground turkey

  • 1/2 cup reduced-fat feta cheese

  • 4 tsp minced garlic

  • 1 small red onion, diced

  • 1 cup spinach

  • 1/2 tsp oregano

  • 1 tsp sea salt

  • 1/2 tsp pepper

Homemade Tzatziki:

  • 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt

  • 1/2 tsp lemon juice

  • 1 large sprig of dill

  • 3-4 sliced pickles, diced

Directions:

  1. Combine all ingredients for the turkey burgers in a large bowl.

  2. Form into patties.

  3. On stove top, heat a large skillet and cook for 5 minutes, flip, then turn the heat to medium low. Cover for the next 5 minutes until all burgers are cooked.

  4. Preheat oven to 375 and cook for ~25 minutes.

  5. Serve with bun, fries, Greek salad, etc.

Title: Salmon Burger
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 salmon fillet

  • 2 tbsp dijon mustard

  • 1 tbsp cilantro

  • 1 tbsp parsley

  • 1/2 tsp salt

  • 1/2 tsp pepper

  • 1/2 tsp paprika

  • 1/4 cup breadcrumbs

  • 1/2 tbsp olive oil

Directions:

  1. Cut the salmon fillet into 1-inch pieces.

  2. In a food processor or blender, add salmon cubes, mustard, herbs, salt, pepper, and paprika.

  3. Pulse until mixed together well. There should be some small chunks.

  4. Transfer salmon mixture to a medium-sized bowl.

  5. Add the breadcrumbs and mix with a spatula until combined.

  6. Evenly divide the salmon mixture into four portions (about 4-oz. each) then shape into patties.

  7. Cook on the stovetop over medium high heat until the fillet is golden brown.

  8. Flip and let it cook for a few more minutes.

Title: Ground Turkey Sweet Potato Bake
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb ground turkey

  • 2 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and diced

  • 2 zucchini, diced

  • 2/3 cup shredded parmesan cheese

  • 1 tsp garlic powder

  • 1 tsp rosemary

  • 5 tbsp olive oil

  • 1/4 tsp salt and pepper

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400°F.

  2. Place in a large baking dish and toss the diced sweet potatoes with 2 tbsp olive oil, 1/2 tsp garlic powder, 1/2 tsp rosemary, salt, and pepper.

  3. Bake the sweet potatoes for 30 minutes.

  4. While sweet potatoes are in the oven, sauté the ground turkey in a pan with 1 tbsp olive oil, 1 tsp garlic powder, 1/2 tsp rosemary, salt, and pepper.

  5. Remove the sweet potato from the oven.

  6. Layer the ground turkey and diced zucchini on top of the sweet potatoes.

  7. Bake for 10 minutes.

  8. Add in an additional 2 tbsp olive oil, mix, and top with the shredded parmesan cheese.

  9. Bake for 10 minutes.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving: 373 calories, 20 g fat, 14 g carbohydrates, 3 g fiber, 35 g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Ground Turkey Sweet Potato Bake

Title: Blueberry Coconut Chia Seed Pudding
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 cup unsweetened coconut milk

  • 1/4 cup water

  • 1 tsp vanilla extract

  • 6 tbsp chia seeds

  • 1.5 cup frozen blueberries

  • 2 tbsp water

Directions:

  1. You will need a container with an airtight lid. A Mason jar works best.

  2. Pour coconut milk first. Then, add in the chia seeds, 1/4 cup water, and vanilla extract.

  3. Put the top on and shake it for 15 seconds.

  4. Add frozen blueberries and 2 tbsp water to a sauce pan and heat on medium.

  5. After about 3-5 minutes, smash the blueberries.

  6. Reduce the heat to medium-low to simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.

  7. Once cooled, add the sauce on top of the chia pudding.

  8. Put the container in the refrigerator for 4 hours.

  9. Take it out and stir it up and enjoy!

Title: Lightened Up Green Bean Casserole
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb fresh green beans, trimmed and cut into bite-sized pieces

  • 2bsp olive oil

  • 1 small onion, finely chopped

  • 2 cloves garlic, minced

  • 8 ounces mushrooms, sliced

  • 2 tbsp whole wheat flour

  • 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth

  • 1 cup unsweetened almond milk (or any other milk alternative)

  • Salt and pepper to taste

  • 1 tsp dried thyme

  • 1 cup whole grain breadcrumbs

  • 2 tbsp grated Parmesan cheese (optional)

  • Cooking spray

Directions:

  1. Preheat the oven: Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).

  2. Blanch the green beans: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add the green beans and cook for 3-4 minutes, then immediately transfer them to a bowl of ice water to stop the cooking process. Drain and set aside.

  3. Make the mushroom sauce:

    • In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and garlic, sautéing until softened.

    • Add sliced mushrooms and cook until they release their moisture and become golden brown.

    • Sprinkle flour over the mushroom mixture and stir well to coat. Cook for 1-2 minutes to remove the raw flour taste.

    • Slowly whisk in the vegetable broth and almond milk. Stir continuously until the mixture thickens.

    • Season with salt, pepper, and dried thyme. Allow the sauce to simmer for a few minutes until it reaches a creamy consistency.

  4. Assemble the casserole:

    • Add the blanched green beans to the mushroom sauce, stirring until well coated.

    • Transfer the mixture to a lightly greased baking dish.

  5. Prepare the topping:

    • In a small bowl, mix the whole grain breadcrumbs with grated Parmesan cheese (if using).

    • Sprinkle the breadcrumb mixture evenly over the green bean mixture.

  6. Bake:

    • Bake in oven for 20-25 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the casserole is bubbling around the edges.

  7. Serve:

    • Allow the casserole to cool for a few minutes before serving.

    • Enjoy your healthier green bean casserole!

Title: Roasted Brussels Sprouts with Balsamic Glaze
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

  • 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar

  • 1 tbsp honey or maple syrup (optional, for sweetness)

  • 1-2 cloves garlic, minced (optional, for added flavor)

  • 2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (for garnish, optional)

Directions:

  1. Preheat the Oven:

    Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).

  2. Prepare Brussels Sprouts:

    • Trim the ends of the Brussels sprouts and cut them in half.

    • Place them in a large bowl.

  3. Seasoning:

    • Drizzle olive oil over the Brussels sprouts, ensuring they are evenly coated.

    • Season with salt and black pepper to taste. Add minced garlic if desired.

  4. Roast Brussels Sprouts:

    • Spread the Brussels sprouts in a single layer on a baking sheet.

    • Roast in oven for 20-25 minutes or until they are golden brown and crispy on the edges. Shake or stir them halfway through to ensure even cooking.

  5. Prepare Balsamic Glaze:

    • While the Brussels sprouts are roasting, prepare the balsamic glaze.

    • In a small saucepan, heat balsamic vinegar over medium heat.

    • Optional: add honey or maple syrup for sweetness. Simmer for 5-7 minutes or until the vinegar has reduced by half and has a syrupy consistency.

  6. Combine and Glaze:

    • Once the Brussels sprouts are done roasting, transfer them to a serving bowl.

    • Drizzle the balsamic glaze over the roasted Brussels sprouts and toss them to coat evenly.

  7. Garnish and Serve:

    • Optionally, garnish with chopped fresh parsley for a burst of freshness.

  8. Serve Warm:

    • Serve the roasted Brussels sprouts with balsamic glaze immediately while warm.

Title: Thanksgiving Kale Salad with Roasted Butternut Squash
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Salad:

  • 1 bunch kale, stems removed and leaves thinly sliced

  • 2 cups butternut squash, peeled and diced into bite-sized pieces

  • 1/2 cup pumpkin seeds (pepitas), toasted

  • 1/3 cup dried cranberries

  • 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled (optional)

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

For the Dressing:

  • 3 tbsp olive oil

  • 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar

  • 1 tbsp maple syrup or honey

  • 1 tsp Dijon mustard

  • Salt and black pepper to taste

Directions:

  1. Roast Butternut Squash:

    • Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).

    • Toss the diced butternut squash with a bit of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

    • Spread the squash on a baking sheet in a single layer and roast for 20-25 minutes or until tender and golden brown. Allow it to cool.

  2. Prepare Kale:

    • In a large bowl, massage the kale with a bit of olive oil for a few minutes until it becomes tender and dark green.

  3. Assemble the Salad:

    • Add the roasted butternut squash, toasted pumpkin seeds, dried cranberries, and crumbled feta cheese (optional) to the massaged kale.

  4. Prepare the Dressing:

    • In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, maple syrup or honey, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.

  5. Dress the Salad:

    • Pour the dressing over the salad and toss everything together until well coated.

  6. Chill (Optional):

    • If time allows, let the salad chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.

  7. Serve:

    • Serve the kale salad in a large bowl or on a platter, and sprinkle additional pumpkin seeds and cranberries on top for garnish if desired.

Title: Sweet Potato Casserole with Pecan Topping
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Sweet Potato Filling:

  • 4 medium sweet potatoes, peeled and cubed

  • 2 tbsp coconut oil or olive oil

  • 1 egg

  • 1/4 cup pure maple syrup or honey

  • 1 tsp ground cinnamon

  • 1/2 tsp nutmeg

  • 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk (or any milk alternative)

  • 1 tsp vanilla extract

  • Pinch of salt

For the Pecan Topping:

  • 1 cup pecans, chopped

  • 1/4 cup whole wheat flour (or other flour alternative)

  • 2 tbsp coconut oil, melted

  • 2 tbsp pure maple syrup or honey

  • 1/2 tsp cinnamon

  • Pinch of salt

Directions:

  • Preheat the Oven:

    Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).

  • Cook Sweet Potatoes:

    • Place the sweet potato cubes in a large pot of water and bring to a boil.

    • Cook until the sweet potatoes are tender, about 15-20 minutes.

    • Drain the sweet potatoes and transfer them to a large mixing bowl.

  • Mash Sweet Potatoes:

    • Mash the sweet potatoes with a potato masher or fork until smooth.

  • Add Ingredients to the Filling:

    • Add beaten egg, coconut oil, maple syrup (or honey), cinnamon, nutmeg, almond milk, vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt to the mashed sweet potatoes. Mix well until combined.

  • Prepare the Pecan Topping:

    • In a separate bowl, combine chopped pecans, whole wheat flour, melted coconut oil, maple syrup (or honey), cinnamon, and a pinch of salt.

    • Mix until the pecans are evenly coated.

  • Assemble the Casserole:

    • Transfer the sweet potato mixture to a baking dish, spreading it evenly.

  • Add Pecan Topping:

    • Sprinkle the pecan topping evenly over the sweet potato layer.

  • Bake:

    • Bake in oven for 25-30 minutes, or until the pecan topping is golden brown.

  • Serve:

    • Allow the casserole to cool for a few minutes before serving.

Title: Greek Crockpot Chicken
Description:

  • 1 cup Greek yogurt

  • Zest and juice of 1 lemon

  • 1 tsp salt

  • 1 Tbsp minced garlic

  • Optional: 1 Tbsp dill

  • 2 lb boneless skinless chicken breast

Directions:

  1. Place chicken breasts in the bottom of the crockpot.

  2. Mix the Greek yogurt, lemon zest and juice, salt, garlic, and dill in a bowl.

  3. Pour half of the marinade over the chicken.

  4. Cook on high for 4 hours or low for 6-8 hours.

  5. Once done, remove chicken and shred with forks.

  6. Drain off all but about 1/2 cup of remaining juices and add your chicken back to the pot.

  7. Mix in the remaining marinade and you’ve got yourself a delicious protein packed dish for dinner.

  8. Serve with rice, pita bread, sliced cucumber, chopped tomato, sliced red onions, and/or fresh parsley.

Title: High-Protein Spinach Artichoke Dip
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 16oz cottage cheese

  • 5.3oz plain fat-free Greek yogurt

  • 5oz frozen spinach (thawed & drained well)

  • 6oz can artichokes (drained & chopped)

  • ½-¾ cup mozzarella cheese

  • ¼ cup parmesan cheese

  • 1 tsp onion powder

  • 1 tsp garlic powder

  • ½ tsp pepper

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400°F.

  2. Thaw and drain spinach & artichokes thoroughly (squeeze out excess liquid).

  3. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.

  4. Pour into an 8x8 glass dish (or medium oval pan) and top with extra cheese if desired.

  5. Bake for 25 minutes, then broil for 1-2 minutes to get that perfect golden top.

  6. Serve with chips or veggies of your choice!

Whether it’s for game day or your next gathering, this dip is a crowd-pleaser that’s as healthy as it is delicious!

Nutrition Data:

Title: Jack-O-Lantern Stuffed Peppers
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 4 large bell peppers (any color)

  • 1 cup cooked rice (white, brown, or your choice)

  • 1 lb ground beef

  • 1 medium onion, diced

  • 1 small bell pepper (any color), diced

  • 2 cloves garlic, minced

  • 1 tsp smoked paprika

  • 1 tsp dried oregano

  • 1/2 tsp chili powder (optional, for a kick)

  • Salt and pepper to taste

  • 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, or your choice)

  • 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes (drained)

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

Directions:

  1. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).

  2. Cut the tops off the large bell peppers and remove seeds and membranes. Lightly brush the insides with olive oil and set them in a baking dish.

  3. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.

  4. Add the ground beef, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until browned (about 5 minutes).

  5. Add the onion, diced bell pepper, and garlic, cooking until softened (about 3–4 minutes).

  6. Stir in the smoked paprika, oregano, chili powder (if using), salt, and pepper.

  7. Stir in the cooked rice and drained diced tomatoes. Mix well and cook for 2–3 minutes to let the flavors meld. Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary.

  8. Spoon the beef and rice mixture into each bell pepper, packing it firmly but not overfilling.

  9. Top each stuffed pepper with a generous sprinkle of shredded cheese.

  10. Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25 minutes.

  11. Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes, or until the peppers are tender and the cheese is bubbly and golden.

  12. Let the stuffed peppers cool slightly before serving.

Tips:

  • For extra flavor, add a splash of Worcestershire sauce or soy sauce to the filling.

  • Swap ground beef for turkey or plant-based crumbles for a variation.

  • Make it saucier by mixing 1/4 cup of tomato sauce into the filling before stuffing.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 4 servings

1 stuffed pepper (493g): 508 calories, 24g fat, 33g carbohydrates, 39g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Jack-O-Lantern Stuffed Peppers

#dinner #easy #recipes #stuffedpeppers #seasonal #highprotein #halloween

Title: Korean BBQ Rice Bowl
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 cups brown rice uncooked

  • 2 heads of broccoli

  2. Cook brown rice as directed on packaging.

  4. Roast veggies for 30 minutes.

  6. Cut steak to desired sized pieces and place in marinade.

  7. On medium heat, place steak in a pan and cook until done.

  8. Remove steak from pan and add onions to the same heated pan.

  9. Cook onions until soft and caramelized.

  10. Optional: Top bowl with green onions and avocado

  11. For a delicious Korean BBQ bowl place rice on bottom and layer serving of eggplant, broccoli, and onions. Add shredded steak and top with green onions and avocado.
